news.title: Mizoram launches scheme to install rooftop solar systems under PM-Surya Ghar
news.para: During a press conference in Aizawl, Rodingliana detailed how the Centre has been offering subsidies for rooftop solar installations to enable domestic power generation through solar energy.

news.title: Indore civic body demolishes two illegal buildings and encroachments
news.para: Following the directives of IMC commissioner Shivam Verma, the corporation's removal department demolished an illegal construction of 3,000 square feet in the minimum open space (MOS) situated at 68 Vishnupuri.

news.title: Union government allocates Rs 882 crore for Bhopal metro project
news.para: Union ministry of housing and urban affairs has allocated Rs 882 crore for the current fiscal year, marking an increase of Rs 269 crore from the previous year, according to reports.

news.title: Gurugram development body razes illegal structures in Behrampur
news.para: As many as 50 police personnel and three earthmovers were deployed to demolish 100 structures, including 25 boundary walls, 10 underconstruction structures, a 1.5 km road and illegal borewells.

news.title: Rajasthan cancels auctions for 22 sand blocks over non-payment of bid amounts
news.para: Fresh tenders were floated, and proposals submitted to the Directorate of Mines and Geology (DMG) to curb illegal practices and streamline the process.

news.title: Chennai: Valasaravakkam plot to transform into lake and eco-park
news.para: Valasaravakkam and Porur neighbourhoods, with more than 5 lakh residents, faced constant flooding, with knee-deep water near metro rail work sites. This caused snarls on the busy Porur-Vadapalani stretch regularly.

news.title: FAC defers approval for Puri greenfield airport over environmental concerns
news.para: Concerns have been raised on the proposed airport's proximity to nesting sites of the endangered Olive Ridley turtles and the habitat of the threatened Irrawaddy Dolphin, besides the sensitive ecology of the coastal area.

news.title: Bharathi Nagar residents halt property tax payments over lack of basic amenities
news.para: They placed a flex banner in their locality, stating that they wouldn't pay property tax until their long-pending grievances were addressed. Their demands include repairing of damaged roads, establishing of proper drainage systems and resolving the issue of sewage getting mixed with drinking water.

news.title: Nashik civic body extends 95% concession in property tax penalty until December 2024
news.para: For payments due in Jan next year, an 85% concession will apply. Previously, the concession in Dec was capped at 85%, but the NMC has increased it to 95% for this month.

news.title: Greater Noida authority to allocate residential plots to 615 farmers within a month
news.para: In Feb, the govt had formed a three-member panel chaired by the chairman of the revenue council, and including the Meerut commissioner and the GB Nagar district magistrate, to address farmers' demands. The committee submitted its report to the govt.

news.title: Labour department conducts camps to register construction workers across Noida
news.para: According to assistant labour commissioner (ALC), Noida, Subhash Chandra Yadav, currently, 15,102 active workers are registered in the district, receiving a weekly subsistence allowance of Rs 1,000 per week under Graded Response Action Plan (GRAP) Stage 4 restrictions.

news.title: Delhi LG directs security, infrastructure overhaul in Narela to boost housing
news.para: The move comes as part of the LG's plans for the redevelopment of the Narela sub-city and transforming it into a hub for educational and sports activities, it said.

news.title: Gurugram development body directs M3M Woodshire to fix unauthorised connections
news.para: During an inspection by GMDA officials, it was found that 450 kilolitres per day (KLD) of water were being drawn through the pipeline, and only 150 KLD reached the condominium.

news.title: E-khata issues to be sorted out in 10 days: Bengaluru civic body
news.para: Thousands of applications are being submitted daily, but persistent delays have left residents frustrated.

news.title: Nearly 47% of PMAY-Urban houses remain unoccupied due to lack of infrastructure
news.para: The parliamentary panel on the housing and urban affairs ministry has stated that the failure to occupy these houses, for “whatsoever reason”, will defeat the very purpose of the mission.

news.title: Shriram Finance sells entire stake in housing finance arm to Warburg Pincus for Rs 3,929 crore
news.para: The company had sold its over 84 per cent stake to the private equity fund for a consideration of Rs 3,929 crore a few months ago, a statement said.

news.title: Gauri Khan gets approval from MCZMA to add two floors to Bandra home
news.para: A presentation on the construction of the additional two floors was made before the Maharashtra Coastal Zone Management Authority (MCZMA), and a structural stability certificate was submitted for the existing building.

news.title: Mahindra Lifespace gets tax demand of Rs 2.09 crore from GST department in Tamil Nadu
news.para: In a regulatory filing, Mahindra Lifespace Developers Ltd said the "company has received order from the Office of the Assistant Commissioner of State Tax, Chengalpattu, Assessment Circle Tamil Nadu, GST imposing tax demand along with interest and penalty."

news.title: AAI seeks pre-feasibility reports for construction of Bhagalpur airport
news.para: The choice of deputy CM-cum-finance minister, Samrat Chowdhary, for the new airport has been Sultanganj. He is of the view that Sultanganj is strategically located and has connectivity with several districts.
